This paper deals with active learning algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the robustness of these algorithms against prior misspecification, which is a common problem in Bayesian methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which further support these sub-categories.
